#X text 68 24 We'll get back to keyboard tracking later in this tutorial. But \, for now \, let's introduce [keytrack] \, which expands on the idea of the last patch. In this example we use the ratio output as a multiplier for the envelope. This way we can shape the sound according to the pitch input. By default \, we have 60 as the reference point and a keyboard tracking amount of 100% \, but we have many shaping options., f 73;
