#X text 274 337 You can also set exponential factors. By default we have '0' (which linear and so is '1'). Negative values flips it vertically., f 43;
#X text 377 412 There is also a signal version., f 15;
#X text 362 472 And there's also a variant that lets you set different amount and exponential values below and above the reference point(s). Check the help file of all these objects as they are rather complex and. Take some time to study them., f 34;
